{"lemma":"لُبْسُ","slug":"لُبْسُ","root":"ل.ب.س","root_slug":"ل-ب-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ل-ب-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"لَبْس","root":"لبس","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":9},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n37504","n37505","n37506","n37507","n37508"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%84%D9%8F%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B3%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to wear; to put on (clothing)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to clothe oneself, to get dressed","examples":[{"text":"طلبتُ منها أن تلبس وتستعدّ للخروج. أخذتها إلى مستشفى خاصّ","english":"I bade her to get dressed and ready to leave the house. I took her to a private hospital […]"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to intermingle (on someone عَلَى (ʕalā))","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"لَبَسَ الْأَمْرَ عَلَى أَحْمَدَ"},{"text":"وَلَا تَلْبِسُوا ٱلْحَقَّ بِٱلْبَاطِلِ وَتَكْتُمُوا ٱلْحَقَّ وَأَنْتُمْ تَعْلَمُونَ","english":"Do not mix truth with falsehood or hide the truth knowingly."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to coat, to cover"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of لَبِسَ (labisa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"covering, tegument","examples":[{"text":"هَلْ تَعْلَمُ أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللّٰهِ صَلَّى اللّٰهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ نَهَى عَنْ لُبُوسِ جُلُودِ السِّبَاعِ وَٱلرُّكُوبِ عَلَيْهَا","english":"Do you know that the Messenger of Allah (peace be upon him) forbade wearing the hides of predators and riding on them?"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of لَبَسَ (labasa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"conflation, confusion"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ambiguity"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/la.bi.sa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37504","headword_ar":"لَبْسٌ","root":"lbs","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Confusedness"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing or an affair or a case; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labasN","text_ar":"لَبَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) [and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lubosN","text_ar":"لُبْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lubosapN","text_ar":"لُبْسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labuwsapN","text_ar":"لَبُوسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lubuwsapN","text_ar":"لُبُوسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"have the same, or a similar, signification.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY raA^oyihi labosN","text_ar":"فِى رَاْيِهِ لَبْسٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In his judgment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opinion, is confusedness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY AlA^amori lubosapN","text_ar":"فِى الاَمْرِ لُبْسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, * A, Msb, K *) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lubosN","text_ar":"لُبْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, Msb.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case, is confusedness, and dubiousness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K; *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obscureness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"want of clearness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Hadiyvihi lubosapN","text_ar":"فِى حَدِيثِهِ لُبْسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In his discourse is confusedness and dubiousness; it is not clear."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY kalaAmihi labuwsapN","text_ar":"فِى كَلَامِهِ لَبُوسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lubuwsapN","text_ar":"لُبُوسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In his language is confusedness and dubiousness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b2-  Also, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confusedness of darkness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the beginning of night."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.)"}],"source_refs":["M"]},{"entry_id":"n37505","headword_ar":"لُبْسٌ","root":"lbs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labosN","text_ar":"لَبْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places:       -A2-  and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"libaAsN","text_ar":"لِبَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n37506","headword_ar":"لِبْسٌ","root":"lbs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"libaAsN","text_ar":"لِبَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in five places: ―         -b2-  and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"libosapN","text_ar":"لِبْسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n37507","headword_ar":"لَبَسٌ","root":"lbs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labosN","text_ar":"لَبْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n37508","headword_ar":"لَبِسٌ","root":"lbs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing clothing, dress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apparel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a possessive epithet. (Sb, M.)"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}